        <updateDate>2021-07-08T19:15:29Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Stop CO Poisoning Exposures Act or the</b> <b>SCOPE Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Transportation to require that automobile manufacturers install technology in each motor vehicle equipped with a keyless ignition device and an internal combustion engine to automatically shut off the motor vehicle after the motor vehicle has idled for a specified period of time to prevent carbon monoxide poisoning.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
